-- Russia Sets Grain-Price Triggers for State Inventories
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 2012-05-23T07:25:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-23/russia-sets-grain-price-triggers-for-state-inventories.html
Russia’s Agriculture Ministry set out
the  price levels  that will trigger grain purchases from farmers
to state stockpiles in the marketing year starting July 1,
according to an order published in  Rossiyskaya Gazeta .  The state will start buying grains from the new crop for
inventories if domestic prices fall to the prescribed levels to
support farmers’ incomes, according to the order.  The price for third-grade milling wheat was set at 5,300
rubles ($169) a metric ton in the European part of Russia and
5,000 rubles in Asian areas. Prices for fourth-grade milling
wheat were set at 4,900 rubles in European areas and 4,700
rubles in the Asian territories.  The level for feed wheat will be 4,550 rubles for  Europe 
and 4,350 rubles for  Asia . The level will be 4,100 rubles for
milling rye, 4,250 rubles for feed barley and 4,650 rubles for
corn across the country, according to the order.  To contact the reporter on this story:
